<http://identifiers.org/rgd/1309009>
        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4173  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Cultured hippocampal neurons (17 days in vitro; DIV17) were immunostained with antibodies against liprina1 and CamKIIa and imaged using confocal microscopy. A punctate pattern of Liprin-alpha 1 was shown as previously described (Ko et al., 2003; Shin et al., 2003; Wyszynski et al., 2002), co- localizing with CaMKIIa in dendritic spines (Figure 1A). Liprin-alpha 1 puncta also showed extensive overlap with PSD-95, a postsynaptic density protein, and with bassoon, a pre- synaptic active zone protein (Figure 1B), indicating the presence of Liprin-alpha 1 at synapses. The intensity of liprina staining was generally weaker and more variable than the staining of these synaptic markers, such that some synapses had robust liprina staining while other synapses showed undetectable signal (Figures 1A and 1B). Quantification revealed that. Experimental description: Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) rat brains. (Couldn't locate exact species information)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4173" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

